item.title: Prefetch URLs
item.description: Prefetch URLsURL prefetching means that Cloudflare pre-populates the cache with content a visitor is likely to request next. This setting — when combined with additional setup — leads to a higher cache hit rate and thus a faster experience for the user. ​​ Availability Free Pro Business Enterprise Availability No No No Yes ​​ Setup For Cloudflare to start prefetching URLs, you will need to enable the feature and include a list of URLs to prefetch.
